repnme.cdata!: Malaysia - Sixth FELDA Land Settlement Project

abstracts.cdata!:
The project fits in with development
            objectives of the Government to raise productivity and
            incomes, and to reduce poverty. It would consist of the land
            clearing and planning of a minimum 62,000 acres of rubber,
            of up to 10,000 acres of cocoa in a pilot project, and of
            500 acres of annual crops of an experimental basis. About
            6,200 families would be settled in the rubber areas, and
            1,500 additional families would work on cocoa. The present
            incomes of these families fall beneath the poverty line. The
            project includes ancillary roads, settler and staff housing,
            and basic education, health, and community service
            facilities. Project risks are related mainly to the price of
            cocoa, which is, however, a small component, and to cocoa
            pests and diseases.
